(6, 'HM Digital TDS-EZ Meter', 'Solids', '10.95', 'Best Budget', 'Brand & Model: HM Digital TDS-EZ Water Quality TDS Tester\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±2% of reading\r\n\r\nResolution: 1 ppm (parts per million)\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0 to 9990 ppm (0-999 ppm displayed in increments of 1 ppm, 1000-9990 ppm in increments of 10 ppm)\r\n\r\nOperation temperature: 0°C to 80°C (32°F to 176°F)\r\n\r\nSize: 6 x 1.2 x 0.8 inches (15.2 x 3.1 x 2.0 cm)\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Simple and easy-to-use with a dip-and-read method\r\n-Provides quick and reliable readings of Total Dissolved Solids (TDS)\r\n-Affordable price, making it accessible for home use\r\n-Automatic shut-off feature to save battery life\r\n-Hold function allows you to freeze the reading for convenience\r\n-Ideal for testing water quality in aquariums, pools, or drinking water\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Not as precise as higher-end, professional-grade meters\r\n-Requires proper cleaning to ensure long-term accuracy', 'https://www.amazon.com/HM-Digital-TDS-EZ-Measurement-Resolution/dp/B002C0A7ZY/ref=sr_1_1?crid=802TN1Z58LG&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.MOzP2SmrOi6in2BNTz-z9IJDbD7IvM8ZSvSEWOQr3UA_VQwbcoHyuuRo-Cw8JsDgbgyE6zIa-EcukKgBW8l5cIiQnr3qkIF2HGcmvBRt5p4.9ErEOtXvrhNbF76UcfmWnAN0AtAeTq4X6xutQcJfPCE&dib_tag=se&keywords=hm%2Btdsez&qid=1725566644&sprefix=hm%2Btdse%2Caps%2C336&sr=8-1&th=1', 'image6', 0),
(7, 'Industrial Test Systems Chloramines Test Kit', 'Chloramines', '20.10', 'Best Budget', 'Brand & Model: Industrial Test Systems 480655 WaterWorks Free and Total Chlorine WW2 Test\r\n\r\nResolution: 0.1 ppm increments\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0 to 10 ppm\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Easy-to-use dip-and-read strips, providing fast results\r\n-Measures both free chlorine and total chlorine levels\r\n-No additional equipment needed, ideal for quick field testing\r\n-Color chart for accurate comparison of chlorine levels\r\n-Compact and portable, making it suitable for home, pool, or spa testing\r\n-Affordable price for regular use\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Not as precise as digital chlorine meters\r\n-Results can be affected by lighting conditions when comparing to the color chart\r\n-Limited range might not be suitable for professional or high-precision needs', 'https://www.amazon.com/Industrial-Test-Systems-480655-WaterWorks/dp/B00AKAOL78/ref=sr_1_3?crid=2NRGL8MONWS9&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Cu-JcwAp7etJAhMW0P68ZpQRTwwvtzY8JrlE-6UeM9LQnLN8Vw3KHBdd4Qxn1IRPvcqKfPjq2geJwNJ7YAKWnQrykcnLTkK5nsvXacFEIfSKJ6HacP5OpvS3N-M5MIxM3TSUbYRBJdaEkDLfQYpjkzp-cCyN9tdIZUxXq3rtwc-i1Unlvm2CxDoUdkKcemcN6yGojolIvjGq-Af39c9rKByzQ0a1490tOOWBv5EUfsM.JFbXRCZbf_BIJtBNMYg09vQ-2nn1MMQnfhiNKBQRE_w&dib_tag=se&keywords=Total+Chlorine+Test&qid=1725567123&sprefix=total+chlorine+test+strips%2Caps%2C280&sr=8-3', 'image7', 0),
(8, 'Hanna Digital Free Chlorine Meter HI710 (Buy also HI711)', 'Chloramines', '79.99', 'Best Overall', 'Brand & Model: Hanna Instruments HI701 Checker HC Handheld Colorimeter for Free Chlorine\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±0.03 ppm ±3% of reading\r\n\r\nResolution: 0.01 ppm\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0.00 to 2.50 ppm\r\n\r\nOperation temperature: 0°C to 50°C (32°F to 122°F)\r\n\r\nSize: 3.4 x 2.4 x 1.5 inches (8.6 x 6.1 x 3.75 cm )\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Highly accurate readings for free chlorine, with a precision of ±0.03 ppm\r\n-Clear digital display for easy-to-read results\r\n-Compact and portable design for use at home or in the field\r\n-Simple operation with a single button press to take measurements\r\n-Better precision than traditional test strips, ideal for pools, drinking water, or aquarium use\r\n-Comes with reagents, testing cuvettes, and batteries for immediate use\r\n-Affordable price for a colorimeter with this level of accuracy\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Measures free chlorine only, no total chlorine measurement, Chloramines (Combined Chlorine)=Total Chlorine−Free Chlorine\r\n-Limited range up to 2.50 ppm, may not be suitable for testing higher chlorine levels\r\n-Reagents need to be purchased for ongoing testing', 'https://www.amazon.com/Hanna-Instruments-HI701-Handheld-Colorimeter/dp/B003IKNJMA/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2QQOEZR3O6KO7&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.orQEWRuIV8Ex5QHP8LjTZkAH6KEORibqgcV2W2Jz0EfBUQI0y1yzqusU9JPel7-WM5j0b2683Xgmn14JqRlS0hwLI2imxcXdtuSVecYOHek1xsXP_0zM8PCLF9mU8fFZYCkYZq-WS97CVsj24M6jM45IMJaGKcueprCNDy1XCc5oej_BOkK5nZX0GlTD_hcI8dMeRxh9KAjyM20p5ipdgVZZU2R5sFmR9MzEE6tosHQ.zeqeGqnYJ4EO0X8FTKzgJ3yYxX4xLP0J5xQbzxMOZZs&dib_tag=se&keywords=Hanna+Instruments+HI701+Checker+HC&qid=1725517098&sprefix=hanna+instruments+hi701+checker+hc%2Caps%2C492&sr=8-1', 'image8', 0),
(11, 'Envig Digital TOC Meter', 'Organic Carbon', '69.99', 'Best Budget', 'Brand & Model: Envig Digital Drinking Water Tester\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±1% of reading\r\n\r\nResolution: 0.01 mg/L\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0 to 10 mg/L\r\n\r\nOperation temperature: 10°C to 40°C (50°F to 104°F)\r\n\r\nSize: 6.5 x 0.75 x 0.83 inches (16.5 x 1.9 x 2.1 cm)\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Specifically designed for measuring Total Organic Carbon (TOC), providing critical data on organic matter in drinking water\r\n-High accuracy and resolution for precise TOC readings\r\n-Digital display for easy-to-read results\r\n-Compact and portable, suitable for on-site and home testing\r\n-Quick response time, delivering fast TOC measurements\r\n-Battery-powered with automatic shut-off to conserve battery life\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Higher price compared to basic water testers\r\n-Requires proper calibration and maintenance for accurate long-term use\r\n-The sensor head is waterproof, but not the entire body.\r\n', 'https://www.amazon.com/Analyzer-Bacteria-Pesticide-Detection-Drinking/dp/B08HNJLMP4/ref=sr_1_3?crid=23SWNQUK2TTLE&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.VLnHtz8K0tBnXq-b0Rqt3KeIKYtm5npe3R_ueyUAQPAmHJd8VWJTt0Kj-6Ij-tJsaYqtqZuAnGBF02_BgOjeQs2r_BzfTV3ASNvmD1-RJoO0W4vaM_MHJslyLyIpe5ed3jhFXa1IbW31tEISIsGaRhXQ_PLDwNsjxNvQpzkEVJdxgj37hHG_aHS_xnZOysWtOs0uWo5cE9ihlzNYKbS-W1-4CDl8kvg9sveul04fBwk._HrB3M2CSnjtoS2rmO96CH_LxcnWeNeph7M0af6vP7E&dib_tag=se&keywords=toc+test&qid=1725527172&sprefix=toc+test%2Caps%2C377&sr=8-3', 'image11', 0),
(9, 'Quantofix Sulfate Test Kit', 'Sulfate', '41.90', 'Best Budget', 'Brand & Model: Macherey-Nagel Quantofix Sulfate Test Strips (91329)\r\n\r\nResolution: 100 mg/L \r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 400 to 1600 mg/L \r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Easy-to-use test strips for quick sulfate detection\r\n-No complex equipment needed, just dip the strip and compare the color to the chart\r\n-Suitable for both home and industrial water testing\r\n-Compact and portable, ideal for on-the-go testing\r\n-Provides fast results in just minutes\r\n-Good value for 100 strips, allowing multiple tests\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Limited to a sulfate-specific test, does not measure other water quality parameters\r\n-Semi-quantitative, so results are based on visual comparison with a color chart, which can be less precise than digital meters\r\n-May not be suitable for lower concentration sulfate detection due to its range starting at 400 mg/L', 'https://www.amazon.com/Macherey-Nagel-91329-Quantofix-Sulfate-Strips/dp/B00S1UL4KQ/ref=sr_1_4?crid=17L68M6MZ0EH&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.12GeYHuBaaNIE0FaizNtyNjvYQr2ylhwc1tIwLE2P2Vb378m2HTKYbpDxZ7QCHkQZTyM6ITLFxTpIAeIKVfTDdWgEH3tw8SEC1ut8mST_IV0Ef9UR3vvw3IYJ7Dsg5v1PNcu9i8hn3bt67r9kcuIxQEoI019NuqYahSTZtsF9eWAHI-6wurHiEzFbUKf3OhoanLQZydRo4aXTDIn93dtU64UKCr_MtMrUjOiA4rAKA0.w9WuSHBrSayh_2YlXsVef8qh8w8i2F7v9sWQYeGdujg&dib_tag=se&keywords=Sulfate+Test&qid=1725523969&sprefix=sulfate+test%2Caps%2C656&sr=8-4', 'image9', 0),
(10, 'Hach Sulfate Test Kit', 'Sulfate', '151.00', 'Best Overall', 'Brand & Model: Hach 225100 Sulfate Test Kit\n\nAccuracy: ±10 mg/L\n\nResolution: 10 mg/L\n\nMeasuring range: 10 to 100 mg/L (Sulfate concentration)\n\nPros:\n-Highly accurate, specifically designed for precise sulfate measurements\n-Wide range of 10 to 100 mg/L, ideal for lower sulfate concentrations\n-Includes reagents and necessary equipment for immediate testing\n-Color comparison method provides reliable visual results\n-Trusted brand for water quality testing, suitable for both field and lab use\n-Comes in a durable, portable case for ease of transport\n\nCons:\n-Requires preparation of reagents, which may be more time-consuming than test strips\n-More expensive compared to simpler sulfate test methods\n-Limited to sulfate testing, does not measure other water quality parameters\n', 'https://www.amazon.com/Hach-225100-Sulfate-Test-Model/dp/B00N3ZEF32/ref=sr_1_14?crid=17L68M6MZ0EH&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.12GeYHuBaaNIE0FaizNtyNjvYQr2ylhwc1tIwLE2P2Vb378m2HTKYbpDxZ7QCHkQZTyM6ITLFxTpIAeIKVfTDdWgEH3tw8SEC1ut8mST_IV0Ef9UR3vvw3IYJ7Dsg5v1PNcu9i8hn3bt67r9kcuIxQEoI019NuqYahSTZtsF9eWAHI-6wurHiEzFbUKf3OhoanLQZydRo4aXTDIn93dtU64UKCr_MtMrUjOiA4rAKA0.w9WuSHBrSayh_2YlXsVef8qh8w8i2F7v9sWQYeGdujg&dib_tag=se&keywords=Sulfate+Test&qid=1725523969&sprefix=sulfate+test%2Caps%2C656&sr=8-14', 'image10', 0),
(12, 'Hach Trihalomethanes Reagent Set', 'Trihalomethanes', '250.00', 'Best Overall', 'Brand & Model:Hach Total Trihalomethanes (THM) Reagent Set\n\nSensitive: Detection limit of 10 ppb (THMplus detects trihalomethanes and haloacetic acids. The aggregate concentration is reported as ppb chloroform.)\n\nMeasuring range: 10 - 600 µg/L\n\nOperation: Requires mixing of reagents and comparison to a color chart or use of a colorimeter for analysis\n\nPros:\n-Cost effective, less expensive than sending samples to outside labs\n-Designed specifically for measuring Total Trihalomethanes, which are important indicators of water quality and potential disinfection byproducts\n-Provides detailed information on THM concentrations, which is critical for ensuring water safety\n-Fast results, quickly screen multiple samples, for prompt system adjustments.\n-Suitable for both field and laboratory use\n\nCons:\n-Requires preparation and handling of chemicals, which may involve more time and care compared to simple test strips\n-Higher cost compared to basic water testing kits\n-Interpretation of results may require experience or additional equipment, such as a colorimeter or spectrophotometer', 'https://www.hach.com/p-total-trihalomethanes-thm-reagent-set/2790800', 'image12', 0),
(13, 'KUIDAMOS Digital Turbidity Meter', 'Turbidity', '130.52', 'Best Budget', 'Brand & Model: KUIDAMOS Digital Turbidity Meter\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±0.1 NTU (Nephelometric Turbidity Units)\r\n\r\nResolution: 0.01 NTU\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0 to 200 NTU \r\n\r\nSize: 14.17 x 10.24 x 5.51 inches (36 x 26 x 14 cm)\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-90 Degree Scattered Light principle for measuring turbidity with good linearity\r\n-Microcomputer configuration with average measurement mode and data storage\r\n-Provides accurate and precise turbidity measurements, essential for assessing water clarity\r\n-Digital display for easy reading and interpretation of results\r\n-Compact and portable, suitable for field or laboratory use\r\n-Often includes features such as automatic calibration, data hold, and auto shut-off\r\n-Can measure a wide range of turbidity levels, making it versatile for different applications\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Higher price compared to simpler turbidity test kits or visual comparison methods\r\n-Requires regular calibration and maintenance to ensure accuracy\r\n-Battery-operated, so battery life needs to be monitored', 'https://www.amazon.com/Turbidity-Accurate-Linearity-Beverage-Industries/dp/B0D7H2MJY9/ref=sr_1_26?crid=1TJF6JBTRJQ8H&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.tOuL9u8ZX81CT3VNLCQjMgAC7inPQlQOFPMxAygecbxfYDcvXPRS1xqagcAcPZFDZ7EDgB1ecXhRx_EjVdi80cbmrUDbX4u9DbUlRsMo1p8cxjxV3Z-v4_VM13l_wru4imXxzx2Vl6Pn3RDz8PCCSWzdDqqgW371sDWlaIKrsr4.1FwUVOMiMrwAWsuAvLSSsAh8GlrlEqg_6UcFMtn7KWY&dib_tag=se&keywords=turbidity+meter&qid=1725529135&sprefix=turbidity%2Caps%2C329&sr=8-26', 'image13', 0),
(14, 'Apera Instruments Digital Turbidity Meter', 'Turbidity', '585.51', 'Best Premium', 'Brand & Model: Apera Instruments AI481 TN400 Portable Turbidity Meter\n\nAccuracy: ≤ ±2 % of reading± stray light\n\nResolution: 0.01/0.1/1 NTU\n\nMeasuring range: 0 to 1000 NTU, automatic range selection: 0.01 to 19.99 NTU; 20.0 to 99.9 NTU; 100 to 1000 NTU.\n\nOperation temperature: 0°C to 50°C (32°F to 122°F)\n\nSize: 12.2 x 11.81 x 4.33 inches (30.99 x 30.00 x 11.02 cm)\n\nPros:\n-High accuracy and precision, with a wide measuring range up to 1000 NTU\n-The test kit comes with 4 vials of AMCO high-molecular polymer turbidity standard solutions (0 NTU, 20.0 NTU, 100 NTU, 800 NTU), which are EPA approved primary standards that are safe, non-toxic and disposable\n-Digital display with clear, easy-to-read results\n-Portable and user-friendly, suitable for both field and laboratory testing\n-Includes features such as automatic calibration, data hold, and auto shut-off to extend battery life\n-Includes a protective case and is designed to be durable for various environments\n\nCons:\n-Higher price compared to basic turbidity test kits or simpler meters\n-Requires periodic calibration to maintain accuracy\n-Battery-operated, so battery management is necessary for continuous use', 'https://www.amazon.com/Apera-Instruments-Portable-Turbidity-Accuracy/dp/B01F34Y7L0/ref=sr_1_5?crid=1TJF6JBTRJQ8H&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.lT5q5U0IOxHcdq5hY1x_Z2UNHXpNo3VPYd8qh21_4An4d0Tfz_pRdyZFAPK4qe6azLldpC27Sl7yCTPlLAk-RB4eHAm8HjkO477Gc9cKhUaFZ-3MFs-8cI4du7O7X6NGoa7qnR7Y2MKICxWv3zvzS4FAy970aKSZtOBrvptS23cvggMEiRNw6toSE3J_YWZBjqyaw_moMUo93_wgBvJGbKYWE0ClGYAEwcyXGuXB9rk.oh6Ji5NuHylDARNt6LxmvX3ndG9I_-bL4fSg1NfX_DQ&dib_tag=se&keywords=turbidity+meter&qid=1725530508&sprefix=turbidity%2Caps%2C329&sr=8-5', 'image14', 0),
(15, '‎3 in 1 HoneForest Multimeter', 'Multimeter, Conductivity, Solids', '13.96', 'Best Budget Multimeter', 'Brand & Model: HoneForest HFTDS-M7 Water Quality Tester\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±2% of reading\r\n\r\nResolution: 1 ppm for TDS, 1 µs/cm for Conductivity\r\n\r\nMeasuring range:\r\nTDS: 0 to 9999 ppm\r\nConductivity: 0 to 9990 µs/cm\r\n\r\nOperation temperature: Typically 0°C to 50°C (32°F to 122°F)\r\n\r\nSize: 6.29 x 1.14 x 0.59 inches (16.0 x 2.9 x 1.5 cm)\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Multi-parameter testing, including TDS and Conductivity\r\n-Equipped with backlit LCD for easy reading. If TDS≤40, the backlit color is green, If TDS>40, the backlit color is red.\r\n-A colorful TDS chart on the back to explains ppm readings.\r\n-Digital display for easy reading of results\r\n-Simple operation with easy-to-use interface\r\n-Affordable price, making it accessible for home use\r\n-Includes features such as automatic temperature compensation, automatic calibration and data hold function\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Lower accuracy compared to high-end, professional meters\r\n-Limited range for TDS might not be suitable for extreme conditions\r\n-Battery-powered, requiring periodic battery replacement', 'https://www.amazon.com/Accurate-HoneForest-Temperature-0-9990ppm-Aquariums/dp/B073713G5F/ref=sr_1_3?crid=2CT3NGS1XRZY0&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.rdBC29fWzTz8fuOsabloFPn7Ym2tIAquKBPa4IVhmiJVZ0cr7bm-ByIB79kGhAEvaSQk6MrfgEuH1dPfph8LHQq6vNVldvHVpG8hswyxceptjUXePGzv-WZZOAr3bFNJFyhgNlSFLjNMH9VjttxkH5qFb1vgfrtBktaRf6RM080GSG0S1zRXhp_Gp4UhLX09XkKmC3MWp-Gc4LRoWW8YUMBPJU82y4GstrbK6GJmZIo.RBN_lX-2LCSU3epMwl9ZxNHHabUrl5D99v2vmucTJe0&dib_tag=se&keywords=ec+meter&qid=1725525308&sprefix=ec+met%2Caps%2C361&sr=8-3', 'image15', 0),
(16, '5 in 1 APERA INSTRUMENTS Multi-Parameter', 'Multimeter, Solids, pH, Conductivity', '128.95', 'Best Overall Multimeter', 'Brand & Model: APERA INSTRUMENTS AI316 Premium Series PC60 5-in-1 Pocket Tester Kit\n\nAccuracy:\npH: ±0.01 pH\nEC (Conductivity): ±1% of reading\nTDS: ±2% of reading\n\nResolution:\npH: 0.01 pH\nEC (Conductivity): 0.1 µS\nTDS: 0.1 ppm\n\nMeasuring range:\npH: -2.00 to 16.00 pH\nEC (Conductivity): 0 to 20,000 µS/cm \nTDS: 0.1ppm to 10.0 ppt\n\nOperation temperature: 0°C to 50°C (32°F to 122°F)\n\nSize: 7 x 1.6 x 1.6 inches (17.78 x 4.06 x 4.06 cm)\n\nPros:\n-Multi-parameter testing (pH, EC, and TDS) in one device, providing versatility for various water quality assessments\n-High accuracy and resolution for reliable measurements\n-Waterproof design for durability in different environments\n-Easy-to-read digital display with clear results\n-Features include automatic calibration, temperature compensation, and data hold function\n-Portable and compact, suitable for field and laboratory use\n-Complete kit with ready-to-use calibration solutions, calibration bottles, storage solutions, AAA batteries, and a lanyard all in a portable carrying case\n\nCons:\n-Higher price compared to simpler single-parameter testers\n-Requires periodic calibration and maintenance for accurate results\n-Battery-operated, so battery life needs to be managed', 'https://www.amazon.com/Apera-Instruments-Conductivity-Multi-Parameter-Replaceable/dp/B01ENFOIKA/ref=sr_1_3?crid=DE9PV6F1MUJI&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.VSXJ721qIN_BHLtS5zBPkGNoQ7RxKFas81P-Z8A7VXGN5BLSsYC4jHb-nrWj_EbjKcHkPgUthGBTnwDoQlww1gLsZ1v4dONFNJ9oTGx_iPJwuFf_YMyZ9v1CV4Oldu96bWgMzIrAwYfoKqR96OPqz_FQt3bGZw9w_bSZv1SXqa3Vqz7qbfc80-UCoMxx-d29iAGiFKp2EM8ddtlffTzqdq5C_DN78Z8NblZrnToxc-o.PaTuSp1RFJHWt3swyxAvgpafojaOQO_5WiJD-s1QKeg&dib_tag=se&keywords=Apera%2Btds&qid=1725513422&sprefix=apera%2Btd%2Caps%2C303&sr=8-3&th=1', 'image16', 0),
(17, '5 in 1 Extech Meter Kit', 'Multimeter, pH, Conductivity', '203.99', 'Best Premium Multimeter', 'Brand & Model: Extech EC510 Waterproof ExStik II pH/Conductivity Meter Kit\n\nAccuracy:\npH: ±0.01 pH\nConductivity: ±2% of reading\n\nResolution:\npH: 0.01 pH\nConductivity: 0.1 µS/cm\nMeasuring range:\n\npH: 0.00 to 14.00 pH\nConductivity: 0 to 1999 µS/cm\n\nOperation temperature: -5°C to 90°C (23°F to 194°F)\n\nSize: ‎ 7.3 x 1.6 x 1.4 inches (18.54 x 4.06 x 3.56 cm)\n\nPros:\n-Dual-function meter measuring both pH and conductivity in one device\n-Waterproof design makes it suitable for use in various environments, including fieldwork\n-High accuracy and resolution for precise measurements\n-Digital display with features like automatic calibration, temperature compensation, and data hold\n-Customizable Interface, able to view data in the following units of measure, all at the touch of a button: pH, µS/cm, mS/cm, ppm, ppt, mg/L, g/L, °C, and °F.\n-Includes necessary accessories such as calibration solutions and protective case\nRobust and durable, designed for tough conditions (IP57)\n\nCons:\n-Higher price compared to single-parameter meters\n-Requires regular calibration and maintenance to ensure accuracy\n-Battery-operated, so battery management is needed for extended use\n-No automatic temperature compensation (ATC)', 'https://www.amazon.com/Extech-EC510-Waterproof-ExStik-Conductivity/dp/B004WN6EPG/ref=sr_1_4?crid=2YTPVV1OBJQ19&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.cnwk2rQzK8Cp9sXGLV4WUsbQS4Ez2F18uNUJoVhkWZ-xEHxT9U54IoItX2pTwLK5o6L349-dcP1RQtt-o3B0BRmp-ASmM2i0Gk0s1vPgGVMnTtLxtt27aRPyM_VsiWE660eVO6jNS7pzyFefS6h8SbPb8Hw3_EKSouiudXb3V90GFRLHOuVy-yjHJnIKv8UY2i6QpybIXhTjd2oDZX8DTipqjL6UYgmbNOCCLvucRZ8.-773Ro2kqP6CyzqZ1p6tZZU9i8tfWG-_NxjYA_7F_-A&dib_tag=se&keywords=Extech%2BEC400%2BExStik%2BII&qid=1725526175&sprefix=extech%2Bec400%2Bexstik%2Bii%2Caps%2C471&sr=8-4&th=1ASmM2i0Gk0s1vPgGVMnTtLxtt27aRPyM_VsiWE660eVO6jNS7pzyFefS6h8SbPb8Hw3_EKSouiudXb3V90GFRLHOuVy-yjHJnIKv8UY2i6QpybIXhTjd2oDZX8DTipqjL6UYgmbNOCCLvucRZ8.-773Ro2kqP6CyzqZ1p6tZZU9i8tfWG-_NxjYA_7F_-A&dib_tag=se&keywords=Extech%2BEC400%2BExStik%2BII&qid=1725526175&sprefix=extech%2Bec400%2Bexstik%2Bii%2Caps%2C471&sr=8-3&th=1', 'image17', 0),
(46, 'Hanna Digital Total Chlorine Meter HI711 (Buy also HI710)', 'Chloramines', '73.99', 'Best Overall', 'Brand & Model: Hanna Instruments HI 711 Checker HC\r\n\r\nAccuracy: ±0.03 ppm ±3% of reading\r\n\r\nResolution: 0.01 ppm\r\n\r\nMeasuring range: 0.00 to 3.50 ppm\r\nOperation temperature: 0 to 50°C (32 to 122°F)\r\n\r\nSize: 3.4 x 2.4 x 1.5 inches (8.6 x 6.1 x 3.75 cm)\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-Easy to use with one-button operation\r\n-High accuracy and resolution for precise chlorine measurements\r\n-Affordable compared to professional instruments\r\n-LED and silicon photodetector for improved measurement accuracy\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-Limited to measuring total chlorine (cannot differentiate between free and combined chlorine), Chloramines (Combined Chlorine)=Total Chlorine−Free Chlorine\r\n-Small display and may be less durable in harsh environments', 'https://www.amazon.com/Hanna-Instruments-Handheld-Colorimeter-Chlorine/dp/B003IKNJN4/ref=sr_1_3?crid=290SQ34GWL7D1&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.UZroNmGomZe0FVo_0fRtLMGA3p_3mxCWJyi6RpQxM3BuRxJiGRH4WTk7_XTIfZxzAGCKV3XQfsyw8NxQqQ29ja7V3e5W4BNxYlxLXKMT1wcT9UPaPDaDGaWLrPV48_YNvR5IViSlVdnG20-VQAx-TTzOrY3g1QkBXltTSBUyrcXQ0C1CMikw3HduIwUgWxcOhwzSOWvDIrawmrI8SZiFhJr3jQS9nkTCMIQE2YTARcA.V2i7QnAkEWVALh87yM48m35_xCH1cm8fjwah3cRIk3s&dib_tag=se&keywords=total+chlorine+meter&qid=1725685715&sprefix=total+chlorine+mete%2Caps%2C293&sr=8-3', 'image8', 0);

